FT  22 APR 93 / International Company News: Improvements at two Canadian
newsprint groups
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT GIBBENS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MONTREAL
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
TWO large eastern Canada newsprint companies posted improved first-quarter
results, signalling an end to the three-year slump in the industry.
Donohue, controlled by the Quebecor publishing and printing group, reported
profits of CDollars 6.3m (USDollars 5m), or 18 cents a share, against a loss
of CDollars 8.3m, or 26 cents, a year earlier, on sales ahead at CDollars
135m, against CDollars 114m.
Quno cut its loss to CDollars 4.2m, or 30 cents, from CDollars 15.7m a year
earlier, on sales of CDollars 127m, against CDollars 106m.
The Chicago Tribune remains Quno's biggest single shareholder and customer.
