FT  22 APR 93 / Russia to insure foreign investments
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Russia intends to set up a Dollars 1bn (Pounds 667m) insurance company to
help shelter foreign investors against losses if power suddenly changes
hands in the country and their projects are taken over by the government.
The company would 'guarantee foreign investors against political risk in our
country', said Mr Yuri Petrov, chairman of the Russian State Investment
Corporation.
