<HEADLINE>
FT  22 APR 93 / Arts: Today's Television
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTOPHER DUNKLEY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Keith Allen and Peter Richardson who have written and directed BBC2's new
series of The Comic Strip Presents .. seem to think that the idea of a
television programme called 'Gourmet Detective' containing a successful
murder inquiry and two great recipes in each show is a joke. Given the
current state of television they are likely to see the idea pinched and put
into practice within a fortnight. The new series (9.00 BBC2) features all
the familiar comedians: Robbie Coltrane, Adrian Edmondson, Dawn French,
Jennifer Saunders, Alexei Sayle etc. Last week Sister Gabriel, the nun in
Body And Soul, saw the villain having his wicked way with one of the mill
girls up against the factory wall after going-home time. Sister G. rushed
away covering her ears but those experienced in tosh like this may suspect
that the sight and sound could prey on her mind and tempt her to wonder what
all this sex business is really like (9.00 ITV). Given that True Stories is
90 minutes long, it had better not be teasing when it undertakes to discover
the true outcome of the story of Butch Cassidy and the Sundance Kid (9.30
C4).
