<HEADLINE>
FT  21 APR 93 / UK Company News: NatWest Bancorp jumps to Dollars 61m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN GAPPER, Banking Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
NATWEST Bancorp, the US subsidiary of National Westminster Bank, yesterday
disclosed a doubling of pre-tax profits for the first quarter of the year,
marking its fifth quarter of recovery from losses at the turn of the decade.
Net income for the quarter rose from Dollars 30.1m to Dollars 60.7m (Pounds
40.1m). The result included the recognition of Dollars 9.5m of federal tax
benefits which had previously not been recorded.
The bank achieved a 13.03 per cent return on equity (7.03 per cent). Its
ratio of tier 1 capital to risk-weighted assets rose to 7.94 per cent (6.47
per cent) and total risk-asset ratio to 12.69 per cent (10.97 per cent).
Mr John Tugwell, NatWest Bancorp's chairman and chief executive, said the
bank had put a difficult period behind it and was now building on a strong
recovery. He said there had been steady improvements in asset quality.
The provision for loan losses in the quarter was Dollars 30m (Dollars
30.5m), while loan charge-offs fell sharply to Dollars 27.9m (Dollars
61.7m). The allowance for loan losses on the balance sheet was Dollars 612m,
or 4.42 per cent of total loans outstanding.
National Westminster's shares closed 11p up at 472p.
</TEXT>
